        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 13 at 1:58PM EDT until July 13 at 2:45PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>SVRBTV

The National Weather Service in Burlington has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
South central St. Lawrence County in northern New York...

* Until 245 PM EDT.

* At 158 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Pitcairn,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind
damage to trees and powerlines.

* Locations impacted include...
Russell, Pitcairn, Edwards, Fine, Fowler, Clifton, Hermon, Clare,
Lower Oswegatchie, Aldrich, Talcville, South Edwards, Degrasse,
Fullerville, Newton Falls, Star Lake, Balmat, and South Russell.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
